The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Feb. 23: The government today restored the payment of productivity-linked incentives (PLI) to Air Indias functional directors, five months after stopping it. With losses mounting, the Air India board had approved a cut of up to 50 per cent in the monthly PLI for the airlines executive directors and other functional directors in September last year as part of cost-cutting measures.                             
	 Mumbai, Feb. 23: Life Insurance Corporations new business premium declined 53.45 per cent to Rs 4,841,42 crore in January this year from Rs 10,401.13 crore in the same period last year, according to IRDA data.                            
	 Mumbai, Feb. 23: Sanjay Kajaria, chairman of the Indian Jute Mills Association (Ijma), has resigned. This follows differences within Ijma on its role in the agreement with the jute unions that ended the 61-day strike in the industry on February 12.                             
	 Mumbai, Feb. 23: Industrial gases manufacturer BOC India Ltd today said its net profit rose 67.83 per cent to Rs 25.93 crore in the fourth quarter ended December 31, 2009, from Rs 15.45 crore during the same quarter last year.
                                                                                                                          
